#
# PLAN_PATCH_TEMPLATE
#
# Unified diff format template for plan code changes.
# Compatible with: patch -p1 < changes.patch
#
# STRUCTURE:
# - One patch file per plan containing ALL code changes
# - Each modified/added/deleted file gets its own diff block
# - Use unified diff format (--- a/ +++ b/)
#
# PLACEHOLDERS:
#   [FEATURE_NAME]     — Feature being implemented
#   [PLAN_DATE]        — Generation date (YYYY-MM-DD)
#   [FILE_PATH]        — Relative path from project root
#   [OLD_CONTENT]      — Lines prefixed with - (removed)
#   [NEW_CONTENT]      — Lines prefixed with + (added)
#   [CONTEXT_LINES]    — Unchanged lines for context (no prefix)
#   [HUNK_HEADER]      — @@ -start,count +start,count @@
#
# RULES:
# 1. Include 3 lines of context around each change
# 2. New files: use /dev/null as the "a" path
# 3. Deleted files: use /dev/null as the "b" path
# 4. Group hunks logically — one per method/block change
# 5. Include ALL files affected by the plan
# 6. Order: new files first, then modified files, then deleted files
#
# === PATCH FORMAT EXAMPLE ===

--- a/[FILE_PATH]
+++ b/[FILE_PATH]
[HUNK_HEADER]
 [CONTEXT_LINE_1]
 [CONTEXT_LINE_2]
 [CONTEXT_LINE_3]
-[OLD_LINE_1]
-[OLD_LINE_2]
+[NEW_LINE_1]
+[NEW_LINE_2]
+[NEW_LINE_3]
 [CONTEXT_LINE_4]
 [CONTEXT_LINE_5]
 [CONTEXT_LINE_6]

# === NEW FILE EXAMPLE ===

--- /dev/null
+++ b/[NEW_FILE_PATH]
@@ -0,0 +1,[TOTAL_LINES] @@
+[COMPLETE_FILE_CONTENT_LINE_BY_LINE]

# === DELETED FILE EXAMPLE ===

--- a/[DELETED_FILE_PATH]
+++ /dev/null
@@ -1,[TOTAL_LINES] +0,0 @@
-[COMPLETE_FILE_CONTENT_LINE_BY_LINE]

# === GENERATION RULES ===
#
# For each task in the plan:
#   1. Identify every file that needs changes
#   2. Write the complete diff for each file
#   3. Include full method/class context (not just changed lines)
#   4. Ensure patch applies cleanly with: patch -p1 --dry-run < changes.patch
#
# Cost-to-detail mapping:
#   S tasks: Full implementation in patch (< 50 lines typically)
#   M tasks: Full implementation in patch (50-150 lines typically)
#   L tasks: Full implementation in patch (150-400 lines typically)
#   XL tasks: Full implementation in patch (400+ lines typically)
#
# EVERY task must have corresponding patch content.
# No task may be left without code changes in the patch.
